{"source": "docs", "batch_index": 154, "chunks": [{"chunk_id": "6d82b65ceb68", "text": "- `x += 5` means `x = x + 5` (add 5)\n- `x -= 3` means `x = x - 3` (subtract 3)\n- `x *= 2` means `x = x * 2` (multiply by 2)\n- `x /= 4` means `x = x / 4` (divide by 4)", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "3.5 Changing Variables", "chunk_id": "6d82b65ceb68"}}, {"chunk_id": "c82a76f8e5c0", "text": "### 3.6 Practice Exercise\n\n**Challenge:** Create a program that calculates the area of a rectangle.", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "3.6 Practice Exercise", "chunk_id": "c82a76f8e5c0"}}, {"chunk_id": "d8bea5a094d6", "text": "<div class=\"code-block\">", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "3.6 Practice Exercise", "chunk_id": "d8bea5a094d6"}}, {"chunk_id": "1bd6657c45b6", "text": "```jac\nwith entry {\n    # Write your code here\n    width: float = 5.0;\n    height: float = 3.0;\n\n    area = width * height;\n\n    print(f\"The area is {area}\");\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "3.6 Practice Exercise", "chunk_id": "1bd6657c45b6"}}, {"chunk_id": "9c788cdf3fb1", "text": "</div>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "3.6 Practice Exercise", "chunk_id": "9c788cdf3fb1"}}, {"chunk_id": "5ade7e102c25", "text": "---", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "3.6 Practice Exercise", "chunk_id": "5ade7e102c25"}}, {"chunk_id": "aec4dc05a173", "text": "## 4. Making Decisions: Control Flow\n\nPrograms need to make decisions based on conditions. This is where `if`, `elif`, and `else` come in.", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4. Making Decisions: Control Flow", "chunk_id": "aec4dc05a173"}}, {"chunk_id": "2dd6c790ddc9", "text": "### 4.1 The If Statement\n\n<div class=\"code-block\">", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4.1 The If Statement", "chunk_id": "2dd6c790ddc9"}}, {"chunk_id": "efba75789622", "text": "```jac\nwith entry {\n    age = 18;\n\n    if age >= 18 {\n        print(\"You are an adult\");\n    }\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4.1 The If Statement", "chunk_id": "efba75789622"}}, {"chunk_id": "43897b9ece40", "text": "</div>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4.1 The If Statement", "chunk_id": "43897b9ece40"}}, {"chunk_id": "a0876ebfa906", "text": "**How it works:**", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4.1 The If Statement", "chunk_id": "a0876ebfa906"}}, {"chunk_id": "300e31d742ab", "text": "- `if age >= 18` - Check if age is greater than or equal to 18\n- If the condition is `True`, run the code inside `{}`\n- If the condition is `False`, skip the code inside `{}`", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4.1 The If Statement", "chunk_id": "300e31d742ab"}}, {"chunk_id": "a67a0566298d", "text": "### 4.2 Comparison Operators\n\nThese let you compare values:", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4.2 Comparison Operators", "chunk_id": "a67a0566298d"}}, {"chunk_id": "a3660a6986b3", "text": "| Operator | Meaning | Example |\n|----------|---------|---------|\n| `>` | Greater than | `x > 5` |\n| `<` | Less than | `x < 10` |\n| `>=` | Greater than or equal | `age >= 18` |\n| `<=` | Less than or equal | `score <= 100` |\n| `==` | Equal to | `name == \"Alice\"` |\n| `!=` | Not equal to | `status != \"done\"` |", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4.2 Comparison Operators", "chunk_id": "a3660a6986b3"}}, {"chunk_id": "c3e3876fd370", "text": "**Important:** Use `==` to compare (not `=`). Use `=` to assign values!", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4.2 Comparison Operators", "chunk_id": "c3e3876fd370"}}, {"chunk_id": "ebe98e6769a7", "text": "### 4.3 If-Else\n\nWhat if you want to do something when the condition is `False`?", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4.3 If-Else", "chunk_id": "ebe98e6769a7"}}, {"chunk_id": "38fd19285eab", "text": "<div class=\"code-block\">", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4.3 If-Else", "chunk_id": "38fd19285eab"}}, {"chunk_id": "95266a7dcd1d", "text": "```jac\nwith entry {\n    temperature = 72;\n\n    if temperature > 75 {\n        print(\"It's hot outside!\");\n    } else {\n        print(\"It's nice outside!\");\n    }\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4.3 If-Else", "chunk_id": "95266a7dcd1d"}}, {"chunk_id": "352b4ee3d6da", "text": "</div>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4.3 If-Else", "chunk_id": "352b4ee3d6da"}}, {"chunk_id": "0fb0002f4900", "text": "### 4.4 If-Elif-Else\n\nWhat about multiple conditions?", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4.4 If-Elif-Else", "chunk_id": "0fb0002f4900"}}, {"chunk_id": "2edaf3cc2587", "text": "<div class=\"code-block\">", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4.4 If-Elif-Else", "chunk_id": "2edaf3cc2587"}}, {"chunk_id": "8d739aba46da", "text": "```jac\nwith entry {\n    score = 85;\n\n    if score >= 90 {\n        print(\"Grade: A\");\n    } elif score >= 80 {\n        print(\"Grade: B\");\n    } elif score >= 70 {\n        print(\"Grade: C\");\n    } elif score >= 60 {\n        print(\"Grade: D\");\n    } else {\n        print(\"Grade: F\");\n    }\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4.4 If-Elif-Else", "chunk_id": "8d739aba46da"}}, {"chunk_id": "bcd17982e8b8", "text": "</div>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4.4 If-Elif-Else", "chunk_id": "bcd17982e8b8"}}, {"chunk_id": "0226d95d7fc6", "text": "**How it works:**", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4.4 If-Elif-Else", "chunk_id": "0226d95d7fc6"}}, {"chunk_id": "34f4971a1544", "text": "1. Check first `if` - if `True`, run its code and skip the rest\n2. If first is `False`, check first `elif`\n3. Keep checking until one is `True`\n4. If none are `True`, run `else` block", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4.4 If-Elif-Else", "chunk_id": "34f4971a1544"}}, {"chunk_id": "6b43d07dc13e", "text": "### 4.5 Combining Conditions\n\nYou can combine multiple conditions:", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4.5 Combining Conditions", "chunk_id": "6b43d07dc13e"}}, {"chunk_id": "262f6b0076c5", "text": "<div class=\"code-block\">", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4.5 Combining Conditions", "chunk_id": "262f6b0076c5"}}, {"chunk_id": "b1ae15024c51", "text": "```jac\nwith entry {\n    age = 25;\n    has_license = True;\n\n    # AND - both must be true\n    if age >= 16 and has_license {\n        print(\"You can drive!\");\n    }\n\n    # OR - at least one must be true\n    if age < 18 or age > 65 {\n        print(\"Discounted ticket price!\");\n    }\n\n    # NOT - reverse the condition\n    if not has_license {\n        print(\"You need a license!\");\n    }\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4.5 Combining Conditions", "chunk_id": "b1ae15024c51"}}, {"chunk_id": "24a9fba9f041", "text": "</div>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4.5 Combining Conditions", "chunk_id": "24a9fba9f041"}}, {"chunk_id": "24d8a15af9bf", "text": "### 4.6 Nested Ifs\n\nYou can put `if` statements inside other `if` statements:", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4.6 Nested Ifs", "chunk_id": "24d8a15af9bf"}}, {"chunk_id": "a6bf4845021b", "text": "<div class=\"code-block\">", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4.6 Nested Ifs", "chunk_id": "a6bf4845021b"}}, {"chunk_id": "4ee8363cb237", "text": "```jac\nwith entry {\n    weather = \"sunny\";\n    temperature = 80;\n\n    if weather == \"sunny\" {\n        if temperature > 75 {\n            print(\"Perfect beach day!\");\n        } else {\n            print(\"Nice day for a walk!\");\n        }\n    } else {\n        print(\"Maybe stay inside\");\n    }\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4.6 Nested Ifs", "chunk_id": "4ee8363cb237"}}, {"chunk_id": "7e9fcd81619a", "text": "</div>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4.6 Nested Ifs", "chunk_id": "7e9fcd81619a"}}, {"chunk_id": "290aa1f0c71a", "text": "### 4.7 Practice Exercise\n\n**Challenge:** Write a program that checks if someone is a child (0-12), teenager (13-19), adult (20-64), or senior (65+).", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4.7 Practice Exercise", "chunk_id": "290aa1f0c71a"}}, {"chunk_id": "7a557121112f", "text": "<div class=\"code-block\">", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4.7 Practice Exercise", "chunk_id": "7a557121112f"}}, {"chunk_id": "08ed276b468a", "text": "```jac\nwith entry {\n    age = 17;\n\n    # Your code here\n    if age <= 12 {\n        print(\"Child\");\n    } elif age <= 19 {\n        print(\"Teenager\");\n    } elif age <= 64 {\n        print(\"Adult\");\n    } else {\n        print(\"Senior\");\n    }\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4.7 Practice Exercise", "chunk_id": "08ed276b468a"}}, {"chunk_id": "4d29fbdae87d", "text": "</div>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4.7 Practice Exercise", "chunk_id": "4d29fbdae87d"}}, {"chunk_id": "eb54ff1d4396", "text": "---", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "4.7 Practice Exercise", "chunk_id": "eb54ff1d4396"}}, {"chunk_id": "a97ceb5f399f", "text": "## 5. Repeating Actions: Loops\n\nLoops let you repeat code multiple times without writing it over and over.", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5. Repeating Actions: Loops", "chunk_id": "a97ceb5f399f"}}, {"chunk_id": "4dc1ac34e815", "text": "### 5.1 The While Loop\n\nRepeat code while a condition is `True`:", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.1 The While Loop", "chunk_id": "4dc1ac34e815"}}, {"chunk_id": "1ef76f91ea4f", "text": "<div class=\"code-block\">", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.1 The While Loop", "chunk_id": "1ef76f91ea4f"}}, {"chunk_id": "2a47f58b975e", "text": "```jac\nwith entry {\n    count = 1;\n\n    while count <= 5 {\n        print(f\"Count is {count}\");\n        count += 1;  # IMPORTANT: Change the variable or loop forever!\n    }\n\n    print(\"Done!\");\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.1 The While Loop", "chunk_id": "2a47f58b975e"}}, {"chunk_id": "179da7bdf15f", "text": "</div>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.1 The While Loop", "chunk_id": "179da7bdf15f"}}, {"chunk_id": "92710c20657d", "text": "**Warning:** Make sure your condition eventually becomes `False`, or your loop will run forever!", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.1 The While Loop", "chunk_id": "92710c20657d"}}, {"chunk_id": "6eb989f566fe", "text": "### 5.2 The For Loop (Counting)\n\nWhen you know exactly how many times to repeat:", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.2 The For Loop (Counting)", "chunk_id": "6eb989f566fe"}}, {"chunk_id": "aaf460873bca", "text": "<div class=\"code-block\">", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.2 The For Loop (Counting)", "chunk_id": "aaf460873bca"}}, {"chunk_id": "f46e1d054fde", "text": "```jac\nwith entry {\n    # Count from 0 to 4\n    for i = 0 while i < 5 with i += 1 {\n        print(f\"Number: {i}\");\n    }\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.2 The For Loop (Counting)", "chunk_id": "f46e1d054fde"}}, {"chunk_id": "7727bb74a30c", "text": "</div>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.2 The For Loop (Counting)", "chunk_id": "7727bb74a30c"}}, {"chunk_id": "65d2ac58a797", "text": "**Breaking it down:**", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.2 The For Loop (Counting)", "chunk_id": "65d2ac58a797"}}, {"chunk_id": "685d4a0b606d", "text": "- `i = 0` - Start at 0\n- `i < 5` - Continue while i is less than 5\n- `i += 1` - Add 1 to i each time", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.2 The For Loop (Counting)", "chunk_id": "685d4a0b606d"}}], "near_dup_candidates": []}